Given the speeches at Jackson Hole, in Powell's eyes, more interest rate hikes to tame inflation are a must. So called disruptive innovation stocks in what is an (IMHO -- overly) managed fund (i.e. additional mgmt fees), will inevitably seem more risky and investors will be willing to pay less for the increased risk cum additional fees.
There is an underlining wave of money coming into play dough, so ARK is capturing some of it!

It is a narrow path and the market capitulation is near, and the holding on ARK are interesting to say the least. So I and give KW a little room to get more agressive now that price of risk have decline substantially.
Hedgefund marks downs on PE are in the pipeline. Lots of those same HFs also invest in ARKK like names on the public side. Redemptions will hit the public side first due to illiquidity on PE side.

This fund really is a bet on growth tech stocks, mostly based in North America. However, I think the 'growth' portion of the market value has been whittled down so much over the last few months they are probably just trading with the market direction now. Probably unlikely to gain much ground, maybe more likely to fall on further inflation and subsequent interest rate rise news.
